<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>485</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0022</addr>  <route>axt-0022.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. An <em>intensional basis for <tex>D</tex></em> is a
  <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="𝓥-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the condition: for every
  element <tex>x : D</tex>, there is a specified directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="𝓥-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link>  <tex>(I_x,  \iota _x)</tex> on the basis index <tex>B</tex> such that
  <tex>x =  \bigvee  (I_x,  \beta   \circ   \iota _x).</tex></p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>486</anchor>   <addr>axt-002L</addr>  <route>axt-002L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> <contributor><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></contributor><contributor><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></contributor></authors> <title>Preliminary notions</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  In our presentation here, we decouple the notion of a basis for a
  <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> from any kind of compactness or relative compactness
  requirements.
</p><p>  In the context of domain theory, the natural notion of basis <em>should</em>  include such requirements (see for example <link href="axt-001U.xml" type="local" title="Basis for a dcpo"><b>Defn. 2.2.3</b> of Abramsky and
  Jung</link>). As our presentation here is intended to be applicable to a
  class of lattices broader than that of dcpos, however, we attempt to keep the
  presentation free of bias towards a specific
  <link href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/concept+with+an+attitude" type="external">attitude</link>. This is
  our motivation for the aforementioned decoupling.
</p><p>  When the notion of a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> attains a specific
  <link href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/concept+with+an+attitude" type="external">attitude</link>, such as
  <link href="axt-0003.xml" type="local" title="Intuition on the notion of a domain">that of a denotational domain</link>, it is perfectly fine for these
  terms to be overloaded to refer to concepts that include these requirements.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>487</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0022</addr>  <route>axt-0022.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. An <em>intensional basis for <tex>D</tex></em> is a
  <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="𝓥-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the condition: for every
  element <tex>x : D</tex>, there is a specified directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="𝓥-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link>  <tex>(I_x,  \iota _x)</tex> on the basis index <tex>B</tex> such that
  <tex>x =  \bigvee  (I_x,  \beta   \circ   \iota _x).</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>488</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0028</addr>  <route>axt-0028.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>28</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. An <em>intensional basis</em> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex>  for <tex>D</tex> is called an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional basis</link> if <tex>\beta</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-0036.xml" type="local" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>489</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0021</addr>  <route>axt-0021.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author> </authors> <title><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> <meta name="source"><b>Defn. 3.2.7</b> of (<link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">[TdJ]</link>, <link href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk//~mhe/TypeTopology/DomainTheory.Basics.Dcpo.html#4941" type="external"><tex>\dagger</tex></link>)</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex> be a universe. A poset <tex>D</tex> is a <em><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</em> if the join of
  of every <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="𝓥-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> on set <tex>D</tex> exists in <tex>D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>490</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001F</addr>  <route>axt-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author>Ayberk Tosun</author> </authors> <title>𝓥-Family</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <em><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family on a type <tex>A :  \mathcal{U}</tex></em> is a pair <tex>(I,  \iota )</tex> where
  <ul>    <li><tex>I</tex> is a type in universe <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>,</li>    <li>and <tex>\iota</tex> is a function of type <tex>I  \to  A</tex>.</li>  </ul></p><p>  List of formal definitions:
  <ol>    <li>      <link href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk//~mhe/TypeTopology/Slice.Family.html#262" type="external">Fam in UF.Slice</link>      in TypeTopology.
    </li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>491</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0032</addr>  <route>axt-0032.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional spectral basis for a locale</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional spectral basis</em> for a <link href="axt-0008.xml" type="local" title="Frame (type-theoretic)"><tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-locale</link>  <tex>X</tex> is an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> for the frame
  <tex>\mathcal{O} ( X )</tex> (considered as a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-dcpo</link>) that satisfies the
  following two conditions
  <ul>    <li>For every <tex>b : B</tex>, <tex>\beta (b)</tex> is a <link href="axt-002S.xml" type="local" title="Compact open of a locale in UF">compact open</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</li>    <li>      The basis <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> is closed under finite meets. This is to say
      that it satisfies the following conditions.
      <ul>        <li>It contains the empty meet: <tex>\exists  t : B. \  \mathsf{isTop} ( \beta (t))</tex>.</li>        <li>          It is closed under binary meets:
          <tex display="block">\forall  b_1, b_2 : B. \  \exists  b_3 : B \  \beta (b_3) \  \text{is the glb of} \  \{   \beta (b_2),  \beta (b_3)  \} .</tex>        </li>      </ul>    </li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>492</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002F</addr>  <route>axt-002F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional algebraic basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional algebraic basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional
  basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> satisfying
  <tex display="block">\forall  b : B. \  \mathsf{isCompact} ( \beta (b) ) .</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>493</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002D</addr>  <route>axt-002D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> with the further requirement that
  for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="𝓥-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex>  given by the basis satisfies the condition
  <tex display="block">\forall  k : K_x. \  \beta ( \kappa _x(k))  \ll  x.</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>494</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0028</addr>  <route>axt-0028.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>28</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Martín H. Escardó</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. An <em>intensional basis</em> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex>  for <tex>D</tex> is called an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional basis</link> if <tex>\beta</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-0036.xml" type="local" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>